definition: A group of fish sufficiently isolated from other groups that, if extirpated, is very unlikely to recolonize naturally within an acceptable timeframe.
definition_source: Canada's Policy for Conservation of Wild Pacific Salmon Glossary.
definition_source_text: Canada's Policy for Conservation of Wild Pacific Salmon Glossary.

definition: Individuals that were born or reared in a hatchery facility.
definition_source: DFO. (2018). Review of genetically based targets for enhanced contributions to Canadian Pacific Chinook Salmon populations. DFO Can. Sci. Advis. Sec. Sci. Advis. Rep. 2018/001. (Erratum: October 2023)
definition_source_text: DFO. (2018). Review of genetically based targets for enhanced contributions to Canadian Pacific Chinook Salmon populations. DFO Can. Sci. Advis. Sec. Sci. Advis. Rep. 2018/001. (Erratum: October 2023)

definition: Origin category describing whether salmon are naturally produced, hatchery produced, or mixed-origin.
Controlled vocabulary for describing the origin of individual salmon (e.g., natural-origin, hatchery-origin, mixed-origin).
